If anyone wants to use icons without the regular fa classes, but rather applying them to specific elements dynamically.

Example:

```
.upload_button::after {
  @include fa-icon();
  content: fa-icon-var(upload);
}
```

Tested with [node-sass](https://github.com/sass/node-sass) that provides binding for Node.js to [libsass](https://github.com/sass/libsass).

Old Style:

```python
	    "TargetGroupHealth": [
	        [
	            {
	                "HealthCheckPort": "7001",
	                "Target": {
	                    "Id": "i-xxxxxxxx",
	                    "Port": 7001
	                },
	                "TargetHealth": {
	                    "State": "healthy"
	                }
	            }
	        ]
    ],
```

New Style:

```python
"TargetGroupHealth": [
        {
            "HealthCheckPort": "7001",
            "Target": {
                "Id": "i-xxxxxxxx",
                "Port": 7001
            },
            "TargetHealth": {
                "State": "healthy"
            }
        },
```

This will allow the security_monkey watcher to have a new ephemeral section for `TargetGroupHealth:*:Target:Id`

